com.orientechnologies.orient.server.distributed

Class ODistributedResponseManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.orientechnologies.orient.server.distributed.ODistributedResponseManager

  • public class ODistributedResponseManager
extends Object
    Asynchronous response manager. All the public methods have to pay attention on synchronizing access by using synchronousResponsesLock lock.

    TODO: - set flags during collecting of response for fast computation on checking for the status

    Author:
    Luca Garulli (l.garulli--at--orientechnologies.com)

        public boolean waitForSynchronousResponses()
                                    throws InterruptedException
        Waits until the minimum responses are collected or timeout occurs. If "waitForLocalNode" wait also for local node.
        Returns:
        True if the received responses are major or equals then the expected synchronous responses, otherwise false
        Throws:
        InterruptedException
